[3.1 Overview of the SQL Query Language]
    - SQL(Structured Query Language)
    - the standard relational database language.

    1) Data-Definition Language (DDL)
        - provides commands for defining relation schemas, deleting relations, and modifying relation schemas.

    2) Data-Manipulation Language (DML)
        - provides the ability to query info from the db and to insert tuples into, delete uples from, and modify tuples in the database.

    3) Integrity
        - SQL DDL includes commands for specifying integrity constraints that the data stored in the db must satisfy.

    4) View Definition
        - SQL DDL includes commands for defining views.

    5) Transaction control
        - SQL includes commands for specifying the beinning and end points of transactions.

    6) Embbeded SQL & dynamic SQL
        - define how SQL statements can be embedded within general-purpose programming languages, such as C, C++, and Java.

    7) Authorization
        - SQL DDL includes commands for specifying access rights to relations and views.
